        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2985380242" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8125081260867492258">This was an odd book. Most of the book was the Mysterious Stranger story, which was about a teenage boy who meets an angel called Satan. It takes place in 1590 Austria and they&apos;re in the middle of witch burnings where no one feels safe or can trust their neighbor. Satan can do magic and Theodore and his friends are greatly amused. Things turn dark when Satan starts helping their neighbors, but they end up in terrible situations or dead instead. The ending is so odd, but Twain died before it was </span>
  <span id="freeText8125081260867492258" style="display:none">This was an odd book. Most of the book was the Mysterious Stranger story, which was about a teenage boy who meets an angel called Satan. It takes place in 1590 Austria and they're in the middle of witch burnings where no one feels safe or can trust their neighbor. Satan can do magic and Theodore and his friends are greatly amused. Things turn dark when Satan starts helping their neighbors, but they end up in terrible situations or dead instead. The ending is so odd, but Twain died before it was finished so it's hard to say how it would have turned out. <br />There is a short funny story about Twain and his wife buying a burglar alarm which never works that gave me a chuckle. The entire book is short and I would like to know how the Mysterious Stranger was intended to end, but interesting overall. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8125081260867492258" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
